name: Cheer Up Charlie's
directions: Inside when you first walk in the bathrooms are right in front of you.
comment: Not always open as they're a bar, but it's an option at night.

name: 901 Red River St, Austin, TX 78701, USA
directions: Toilets and urinals are what's listed on the doors.
comment: Cheer Up's is queer friendly.

name: Cherokee County Nursing Center
directions: Scattered around the building

name: Pret A Manger
directions: Accessible to the back of the shop. Others down the stars to the left of the entrance
comment: In my experience you can just walk in and use them as they’re usually super busy and don’t mind

name: Crofton Young People’s Centre
directions: You’ll have to ring the door buzzer but somebody will show you where the toilets are
comment: IMPORTANT: This building is part of Wakefield’s Safer Places scheme so will be super accommodating - you just need to explain the situation. Press the buzzer by the door and say you noticed it’s a safer place and ask if they can

name: The Hut
directions: Walk into the centre. Toilets are past the reception desk and to the right just after the pool tables
comment: It’s a community centre so you should be okay. The manager of the centre is a bit funny so if a guy with grey hair is in just pretend you’re enquiring about the times for roller skating or bowling prices. There’s a small cafe too so you could just buy a chocolate bar and go toilet too

name: Burger King
directions: Walk straight into the restaurant. Toilets are to the left of the counter.
comment: You need to be a paying customer but you could probably easily sneak through at peak times

name: Caffe Nero
directions: Straight through the door, past the counter and seating - single unisex accessible toilet on the right
comment: Used many times without buying a coffee, staff are lovely and have let me use it before if I’ve asked politely. Staff member Richard (tall, black hair and super smiley) is real nice with lgbt folk

name: Costa Coffee
directions: Accessible toilet straight ahead on the bottom floor. Unisex toilets up the stairs at the back of the shop.
comment: Probably have to be a paying customer but I’ve used them loads of times before when it’s been busy and it has been fine

name: Starbucks
directions: Walk through the entrance and the toilets are straight in front of you at the back of the shop
comment: Used these before without buying a coffee - but best to be safe if you are nervous. Coffee is always good! Staff are nice and approachable too.

name: Tanger Outlet Malls
directions: Next to Zumiez

name: 222 Mt Hermon Rd, Scotts Valley, CA 95066, USA
222 Mt Hermon Rd, Scotts Valley, CA 95066, USA
Starbucks
directions: To right of registers

name: Ozaukee County Administration Building
directions: Main Floor on west side of building and lower level

name: Thompson Library
directions: On the 11th floor

name: Holiday Inn & Suites
directions: By the pool
comment: Accessible without being a guest. Parking is for guests only but they probably wouldn’t notice or care about your short bathroom trip

name: Tim Hortons
directions: Take a right, in the back.
comment: Women’s room is in view of some tables.

name: Snöåvägen 20D, 771 42 Ludvika, Sweden
directions: To the right when you enter the store.
comment: Free for all!

name: Granitvägen 2, 771 41 Ludvika, Sweden
directions: Directly to the left of the entrance.
comment: Free for everyone, just ask for the key in the betting shop.

name: Laika Press
directions: In the back of the space
comment: Open whenever any of the businesses that share the space have hours!

name: Taco Bell
directions: Outside the restaurant, to the right hand side of the entrance
comment: Unknown whether or not you have to be a paying customer to use

name: The Field Pub
directions: Two single stall women’s rooms, one far back in a hallway to the right, the other near the door to the patio. Men’s room is in the back on the bar side. Has a urinal and single stall.
comment: Patrons are potentially a mixed bag (it’s a cash only Irish pub) but the staff is friendly/supportive and will have your back if you’re not causing trouble.

name: Julie Lehman Psychotherapy and Sex Therapy
comment: Two single stall gender neutral bathrooms available for client use.

name: Kings Mineola Food Market
directions: Inside Exxon Gas Station

name: Jenson-Noble Single-Occupant Restroom
directions: Enter Jenson Noble and head toward Sperati's entrance in the back. Open the doors on the left and it's the door immediately on the right.
comment: A little tricky to find, but there are signs saying "single occupant restroom" that should let you know you're headed in the right direction.

name: Gordon's Tearoom and Restaurant
directions: Back of indoor area.

name: Wiggly Giggly Playground
directions: Right next to the playground
comment: Sink is kinda faulty. Two single stall bathrooms. Pretty empty area.

name: The 459 Commons
street: Off of Highland Rd and South Campus Dr
directions: In the hallway connected to the outside. By outtakes.
comment: Probably best to be an LSU student because it's a dining hall.

name: Cafe Crepe
directions: Go in through the doors, walk in a straight line & you’re there
comment: French speaking staff.

name: Post & Beam Brewing
directions: Two single, non-gendered, bathrooms on the scond floor, across from the bar. Brewery is wheelchair accessible via a small elevator to the right when you enter. The entrance to the building is in the back, at the end of a gravel driveway/ramp; folks with accessibility concerns could probably get the okay to be dropped at the top of the ramp, past the gate.

name: Madison Library District Public Library
directions: Immediately inside the Adult section, the first door on the right.
comment: Remember not to bring library materials into the bathroom.

name: Village Sport Shop Trailside
directions: In the corner by the bar.
comment: Single unisex restroom.

name: Exaloo
comment: At bus station

name: Exaloo
comment: At the bus station

name: Lockeland Table
directions: Back right corner when you walk through the front door.

name: Väla centrum
directions: In several places around the shopping centre
comment: Free for everyone

name: Dukes Farm Foundation
directions: Next to the woman's restroom in the Orientation Center. "All gender"and accessible sign.

name: Night and Day Coffee Cafe
directions: Next to food counter
comment: Single unisex restroom

name: The Phluid Project
directions: Back left of the store past cash register
comment: Clothing store with 2 single unisex bathrooms.

name: Fairway Market
directions: Near the frozen vegetables look for wooden doors
comment: 3 single stall unisex restrooms

name: Whole Foods
comment: Unisex multi stall

name: The Odditorium
directions: To the left right when you walk in
comment: Accessibility is debatable - inside the bathroom is very spacious with hand rails, but the door to the bathroom is very close to the bar

name: Alfred Lerner Hall
directions: Go to back of building (campus side) as the street side is only accessible to students/staff. Enter doors and take a left into the cafe. Go all the way through the cafe and the restrooms are in the back right corner.
comment: Restrooms are gendered and multi stalled, but campus posts signs on door to use the restroom most consistent with you identity.

name: Pop Bar
comment: Not sure if accessible

name: Upstairs circus
comment: Not sure if accessible

name: Alfred Lerner Hall
directions: The street side of Alfred Lerner Hall is only accessible to students/staff. To get entrance without an ID go to the back (campus entrance) of the building and enter. On the left you will see a cafe. Walk through the cafe to the back. Restrooms will be on your right.
comment: Multi stall gendered restrooms. Campus posts signs to use whichever best fits your identity.

name: Flowers For All Occasions
directions: At the back of the bar on the left hand side

name: Poppo's Taqueria
directions: In the back behind the wall with the drink machine

name: Crossroads Center
directions: Two family restrooms past food court, by JC Penney.

name: Piney Run Park Nature Center
directions: Walk towards the fish tank, make a left down that hallway and another left. The two bathrooms are on your right. One has a changing table and is handicap accessible.
comment: There is an entrance fee to get into the park with a car (walking or biking is free) and the Nature Center is not always open. See https://ccgovernment.carr.org/ccg/recpark/pineyrun/PRNatureCenter.aspx for Nature Center hours or call the gate house at 410-795-3274.

name: In Common
directions: Both washrooms in the restaurant are non gendered, one is larger/accessible
comment: For customers

name: Grill 309
directions: From the entrance, head to the right back corner, hallway with two restrooms on the right
comment: Probably customer only

name: John's Incredible Pizza
comment: Must be a paying customer to use. Bathroom is frequently locked for maintenance with no out of order sign or other indication it is not simply busy.

name: Starbucks
comment: No code needed. In back on right

name: Grand Wailea Beach and Pool restroom
directions: Right by the pool desk where you get your pool wrist bands

name: Yogurtland
directions: Have to ask employee for key

name: The Avid Reader
directions: Out the door in the back of the store, to the left from the back door and down the hallway a bit. You’ll reach a dead end. Look to your left, there’s two gendered single stalls.
comment: You have to ask for the key from the bookstore staff beforehand.

name: Starbucks
comment: Get code from cashier (may need to buy something)

name: San Diego
directions: Second terminal, gate 37

name: San Diego airport terminal 2
directions: At gate 37, terminal 2

name: The New Parkway Theater
directions: Accessible in the dining hall prior to the actual theater entrance; in the back right corner.
comment: You should be able to enter & use the restrooms without purchasing anything (unless policy has recently changed).

name: Blue Mountain Bistro To Go
directions: Behind the counter, right when you walk in.
comment: One single occupancy, gender neutral bathroom with locks.

name: Central Alternative High School
directions: Go through the main entrance and turn left. It will be on the left and marked with ‘Staff Only’ in red stickers.
comment: You’ll have to ask the secretary, Mrs. Bair, in the office. She’ll either say yes or have you ask the principal. They happily cater to students and guests.

name: Starbucks
directions: This Starbucks is inside Grand Park.
